What you need to know:

The council said East African member states risk losing USD70 billion (Sh7 trillion) should the countries insist on having the testing done at the borders.EABC is seeking sustainable solutions to reduce the trucks snarl-ups.According to a report released by EABC, 56 per cent of businesses have been affected by cross-border restrictions.In the last three months, it is estimated that Kenya alone has lost USD200 million (Sh20 billion) due to the delays.